## 📌 TASK 13 — Performance Targets

### Hard Targets (Must Achieve)

| Metric | Target | Acceptable Minimum |
|--------|--------|-------------------|
| Role classification accuracy | ≥ 85% | ≥ 80% |
| Role F1 (weighted) | ≥ 85% | ≥ 80% |
| Skill extraction relevance | ≥ 80% | ≥ 75% |
| Score consistency (similar resumes) | ±10 pts | ±15 pts |
| Risk-score inverse correlation | r < −0.7 | r < −0.5 |
| Single resume processing time | < 3 sec | < 5 sec |
| Model file size (total) | < 100 MB | < 200 MB |

### Stretch Targets (Ideal)

| Metric | Stretch Target |
|--------|---------------|
| Role classification accuracy | ≥ 90% |
| Role F1 (macro) | ≥ 85% |
| Skill extraction precision | ≥ 95% |
| Resume processing time | < 1 sec |

---

## 📌 TASK 14 — Failure Case Analysis

### Failure Types to Identify

| Failure Type | Example | Impact |
|-------------|---------|--------|
| **Role Misclassification** | Finance resume predicted as Accountant | Wrong career path suggestions |
| **Skill Miss** | "Machine Learning" not extracted | Lower score, wrong gap analysis |
| **False Skill** | Random word extracted as skill | Inflated score, wrong matching |
| **Score Outlier** | Weak resume scores 90 | Misleading quality signal |
| **Risk Contradiction** | Score 85 but Risk "High" | User confusion, lost trust |
| **Match Failure** | IT resume matches Chef JD at 60% | Recruiter gets irrelevant candidates |

### Analysis Protocol

| Step | What to Do |
|------|-----------|
| 1 | Collect all test-set predictions |
| 2 | Filter for incorrect/inconsistent outputs |
| 3 | Group failures by type (misclassification, score outlier, etc.) |
| 4 | Identify common patterns in failures |
| 5 | Determine if failures are feature-related, data-related, or model-related |
| 6 | Prioritize fixes by impact (how many users would be affected) |

